Look, where I am - pwd

Create a foulder - mkdir study

Go to this foulder - cd study

Create new 3 folders - mkdir Hanna Bananka Karsanova

Go to any folder - cd Hanna

Create 5 files (3 txt 2 json) - touch test1.txt test2.txt test3.txt test4.json test5.json

Create new 3 folders - mkdir dir1 dir2 dir3

List the folder contents - ls -la

open any txt file - cat > test1.txt

write something in this file - write some words

save and exit -  press ctrl c

Go out from folder to up level - cd ..

Move any two files in another folder - mv Hanna/test1.txt Bananka

                                       mv Hanna/test2.txt Bananka

Copy any 2 files in another folder - cp Hanna/test4.json dir1

                                     cp Hanna/test5.json dir2

find a file by name - find /Users -name "test1.txt" 

to view the content in real time - tail -f Bananka/test1.txt

output the first few lines of a text file - head -n2 Bananka/test1.txt

output the last few lines of a text file - tail -n2 Bananka/test1.txt

output the time and date - date




